ted\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":6,\"aggregated\":\"\\\"session\\\": {\\n    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"global\\\",\\n    \\\"dmScope\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n    \\\"identityLinks\\\": {\\n      \\\"me\\\": [\\n        \\\"whatsapp:+27763674298\\\",\",\"cwd\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774004952143}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f2e9ba6a\",\"parentId\":\"70f354e6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-20T11:09:20.847Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Found it. Here's the history:\\n\\n| Config | TUI/WebUI | WhatsApp |\\n|--------|-----------|----------|\\n| **Original** (no `scope` set) | Separate sessions | Own session |\\n| **Current** (`scope: global`, `dmScope: main`) | Shared | Separate |\\n\\n**The split-brain cause:** Original config had NO `scope` setting, which defaults to `per-sender` — creating separate sessions for each connection.\\n\\n**What worked:** Adding `scope: global` made TUI + WebUI share (verified with WebUI test).\\n\\n**What's still broken:** WhatsApp uses `dmScope: main` which routes to a different session.\\n\\n**What doesn't work:** Can't set `dmScope: \\\"global\\\"` (not a valid value).\\n\\n**Question for you:** What's the actual session name when you check `openclaw sessions list`? Is there already a \\\"main\\\" session that everything *should* be joining? Maybe we need to set both to explicitly target the same named session rather than using scope.\"}],\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.5:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":47640,\"output\":605,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":48245,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1774004960845}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"e394e2be\",\"parentId\":\"f2e9ba6a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-20T11:10:00.115Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"System: [2026-03-20